law.text:
The board shall:
Promulgate administrative regulations necessary to carry out the provisions of KRS 309.130 to 309.1399;
Select the examinations for licensure and administer the examinations at least annually;
Establish the application deadline for and score required to pass the examinations;
Process applications and conduct and review the required examinations;
Issue licenses to applicants who meet the requirements of KRS 309.133 to 309.137;
Deny, suspend, or revoke a license to practice art therapy;
Censure, reprimand, or place a license holder or applicant on probation for a period not to exceed one (1) year;
Maintain a current register of license holders as a matter of public record;
Establish criteria for continuing education;
Establish procedures for receiving, investigating, and resolving complaints against license holders;
Conduct administrative hearings in accordance with KRS Chapter 13B for disciplinary actions taken under authority of subsections (6) and (7) of this section;
Approve the level of supervision and experience required for persons seeking licensure;
Assess fees for the issuance and renewal of licenses to cover administrative and operating expenses of the board, and authorize all disbursements necessary to carry out the provisions of KRS 309.130 to 309.1399;
Implement an impaired professional art therapist treatment program;
Establish a code of ethics for license holders;
Establish requirements for supervision and qualifications of supervisors; and
Establish conditions for inactive status and return to active status for license holders.
